AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM, Purge and Charge

Includes:
1. Check for leaks using a leak detector
2. Add freon for sniffer test
3. R&R pressure switches/fan drive switch
4. R&R Refrigerant lines
5. R&R freon compressor and belt, recalculate system oil charge
6. R&R or replace thermostatic expansion valve (TXV) if applicable
7. Replace dehydrator (A/C dryer)
8. Performance tests as outlined in Service manual

Notes:
1. Purging is performed when the part being replaced has significant damage and caused a sudden loss of freon
2. With no freon in the system, it is not necessary to identify refrigerant, recover A/C system, or conduct the initial A/C performance test

FREON COMPRESSOR (NON-ORIFICE TUBE SYSTEM), Replace

Includes:
1. Performing tests per Service Manual instructions
2. Remove and replace component and reinstall all related parts
3. Perform compressor test per manual instructions with internal failure
4. Perform refrigerant identification test, using special tool, prior to recovering refrigerant
5. Recover, replenish refrigerant oil, evacuate and charge A/C system
6. R&R pressure switches/fan drive switch with complete freon loss or internal compressor failure
7. R&R or replace expansion valve with complete freon loss or internal compressor failure
8. Flush and purge A/C system components with internal compressor failure, purge with complete freon loss.
9. R&R A/C compressor drive pulley/clutch coil assembly with CCI compressor.
10. Remove and reinstall drive belt and adjust
11. Replace dehydrator (A/C dryer) with complete loss of freon or internal failure
12. Check for leaks using a leak detector

Notes:
1. Clutch or Minor Leak failure includes charge A/C, Internal failure includes flush, purge and charge A/C

Component Qualifier Code Applies To Hours
CCI Compressor Internal failure A19-100 All Models 3.9
CCI Compressor Front seal or gasket failure A19-101 All Models 2.0
Sanden Compressor Internal failure A19-105 All Models 3.1
Sanden Compressor Clutch or front seal failure A19-106 All Models 1.7
